</font>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubromil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bromil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 12:16:45 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.bbnow.net/gshaw/bear/sbromil.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good place to help PL yer friendly other wizzys:</span><hr size=1> i dont think they have 15k myself i think its more around 10 - 12 k. alot of the pulls i could finish myself if i wanted, some of the pulls i need 1 - 2 more nukes to finish them off. depends on how many times i gotta snare to get em all packed up and tight and ready for AEs. all in all hell ya its fun hehe<br>
<br>
the BIGGEST thing to remember is do not get far ahead of them. do not go around a corner and make them have to climb a wall to get to you, sometimes htey get stuck in the roof and start warping. and the other thing is do not pull them out the ramp into WL are itself. gotta keep em in the cave. if they get near the ramp, they go under the wolrd and warp like mofos <p><BR><BR><CENTER><B>-=Bromil Brimstone=-</B></CENTER><BR><CENTER><I>60 Sorceror of Tarew Marr</I></CENTER><BR><CENTER><I>Minions of Kaer Baar</I></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 8:42:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good place to help PL yer friendly other wizzys:</span><hr size=1> I played around with these guys last night and discovered that they have around 10k hp.  They have low magic resistance, but medium fire/cold resist, so Pillar of Lightning is the tool of choice.  Two wizards of 54+ can pretty easily take down a set of 4 (we avoided or single pulled any shamen we encountered).<br>
<br>
The advice about not getting too far ahead of them is good (and I have the lumps to prove it).  Also important is if you are pulling noids anywhere near a shaman, pull with snare as they will almost certainly have been SoW'ed.  We did pull them out of the cave a bit and didn't have warp problems outside, but your mileage may vary.<br>
<br>
- Armok Komra (Arcis)<br>
59 wizard of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubromil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bromil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/01 3:04:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.bbnow.net/gshaw/bear/sbromil.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Good place to help PL yer friendly other wizzys:</span><hr size=1> hmm must be a problem on TM itself. ill petition it and see what happens. you cant get em out of the cave on TM coz they go under the world everytime.<br>
